<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="722" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="3.[111,649,1103,1383]" box="[113,233,1103,1129]" pageId="3" pageNumber="722">REMARQUE</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[111,649,1103,1383]" pageId="3" pageNumber="722">
Les spécimens identifiés comme 
<taxonomicName authority="(Smith, 1879)" baseAuthorityName="Smith" baseAuthorityYear="1879" genus="Homalictus" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="3" pageNumber="722" rank="species" species="urbanus">
<emphasis box="[448,562,1134,1160]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="722">H. urbanus</emphasis>
(Smith, 1879)
</taxonomicName>
par 
<bibRefCitation author="PAULY A. &amp; MUNZINGER J." box="[220,506,1166,1193]" pageId="3" pageNumber="722" pagination="153 - 166" refId="ref7407" refString="PAULY A. &amp; MUNZINGER J. 2003. - Contribution a la connaissance des Hymenoptera Apoidea de Nouvelle- Caledonie et de leurs relations avec la flore butinee. Annales de la Societe entomologique de France 39: 153 - 166." type="journal article" year="2003">Pauly &amp; Munzinger (2003)</bibRefCitation>
de Nouvelle-Calédonie diffèrent légèrement des spécimens australiens de 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Smith" baseAuthorityYear="1879" box="[277,404,1229,1255]" genus="Homalictus" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="3" pageNumber="722" rank="species" species="urbanus">
<emphasis box="[277,404,1229,1255]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="722">H. urbanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
et se rapprochent de ceux du 
<collectingCountry box="[206,301,1261,1288]" name="Vanuatu" pageId="3" pageNumber="722">Vanuatu</collectingCountry>
. Le nom 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cheesman &amp; Perkins" authorityYear="1939" box="[399,492,1262,1287]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Halictus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="722" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aponi">
<emphasis box="[399,492,1262,1287]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="722">H. aponi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
est disponible pour dénommer les spécimens du 
<collectingCountry box="[492,583,1293,1320]" name="Vanuatu" pageId="3" pageNumber="722">Vanuatu</collectingCountry>
et de 
<collectingCountry box="[115,327,1325,1352]" name="New Caledonia" pageId="3" pageNumber="722">Nouvelle-Calédonie</collectingCountry>
. Le statut de ce taxon est encore à l’étude.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
